Commit Message:
remove 'capture_output'

capture_output was introduced in 3.7, older versions won't work.

Fix display units

We read from Kubernetes kibibytes and also calculate with base 1024,
so also show the appropriate units.

Consider only PODs with configured limits in the summary

Otherwise the calculated overall percentage doesn't make any sense
if we would take usages into account without a set limit.

Add support for -c / --cpu flag (#3)

List configured cpu requests, limits and the current cpu usage when using -c / --cpu flag.
Round humanized usage values to have more accurate numbers

Improve job detection

Skip owner references lookup if we didn't even find a job name label.
Set default for metadata.labels field in case it is missing completely.
Add Flake8, Isort and PyLint configs
Ignore PODs without any containers assigned
Use f-strings and other minor linting fixes, reported by PyLint
Migrate from Travis CI to Github Actions
Add Python 3.9 and 3.10 to Tox and CI environments
